author: Jacob Champion
commit_message:
Don't double-iterate during MultiDict init (#3)

Previously, the MultiDict constructor iterated twice over its argument:
once as a sanity check on its contents, and once again to add those
contents to the dictionary. If a generator was passed as an argument,
the first iteration would drain it, and the resulting dictionary would
be empty.

To fix this, save the contents of the generator in another list. This
fixes #2.

author: Jaen
commit_message:
Fix MyPy type stubs (#123)

The current type stubs can not actually be used from a client
perspective, since MyPy considers the declared classes abstract due to
missing definitions for methods such as `__getitem__`.

The commit add the necessary type definitions to make all the classes
non-abstract and adds a "test" to make sure these type definitions can
actually be used.

author: Sviatoslav Sydorenko
commit_message:
📦🎨 Move package attrs to declarative config

This cleans up `setup.py`, keeping only things that are hard to move.
It puts all possible attrs into `setup.cfg`. It doesn't attempt
making use of `pyproject.toml` for this purpose because it's easier to
maintain separate configs in dedicated files, on scale.
